OL,6,FOn the record he described the core
OL,7,Fvalues of his newspaper for the people
OL,8,Fof Hong Kong as being "carved into
OL,9,Ftheir hearts because they lived under
OL,10,Fthe institution of the British
OL,11,Fcolony." Asked to elaborate on what he
OL,12,Fmeant he said the "rule of law,
OL,13,Ffreedom, pursuit of democracy, freedom
OL,14,Fof speech, freedom of religion,
OL,15,Ffreedom of assembly".
