OL,6,FHis Lawyer asked about his stance
OL,7,Fregarding the independence of Hong
OL,8,FKong and Taiwan which the 76-year-old
OL,9,Fsaid was "too crazy to think about".
OL,10,FHe went on to say that he would never
OL,11,Fallow anyone who advocated the idea to
OL,12,Fjoin his newspaper.
OL,14,FHe was later asked about his
OL,15,Fconnections with the former Taiwan
OL,16,FPresident Tsai Ing-wen and admitted
OL,17,Fthat they had become friends bonding
OL,18,Fover a shared interest in discussing
OL,19,FUS politics.
